latestPosts.caption:
👀 Ever noticed a white film or powdery layer on your niacinamide skincare products? Don’t worry — it’s not expired or contaminated. 💡
This is a common phenomenon caused by crystallization, especially in formulas with a high percentage of niacinamide or when exposed to air for too long. The active ingredient starts to come out of the solution and forms a visible white coating.
✅ It’s usually safe to use, but always check for changes in smell or texture to be sure.
📦 Proper storage (cool, dry place + tightly sealed) can help prevent it.
🧪 Niacinamide is a powerful brightening and barrier-supporting ingredient, and a little crystallization doesn’t mean it’s ineffective!
Save this to know what’s really happening in your skincare shelf! 🧴🔬
